OL,5, Microsoft's revised offer to buy Call  
OL,6, of Duty-maker Activision Blizzard has  
OL,7, been approved by UK regulators.        
OL,9,FThe Competition Markets Authority (CMA)
OL,10,Fsaid the updated bid had addressed     
OL,11,Fconcerns, after it blocked the original
OL,12,F$69bn (#59bn) deal in April.           
OL,14,FMicrosoft will hand the rights to      
OL,15,Fdistribute Activision's games on       
OL,16,Fconsoles and PCs over the cloud to     
OL,17,FFrench video game publisher Ubisoft.   
OL,19,FDespite approving the deal, however,   
OL,20,Fthe CMA criticised Microsoft.          
